2015-06-04 12:01:42	+emptythevoid	good luck
2015-06-04 12:01:48	-->	Wyndgem (Wyndgem@TS-epp.ivc.k0d9k9.IP) has joined #frogpants
2015-06-04 12:03:27	@KAPT_Kipper	We are partially done, phase A is done and now work has started on B
2015-06-04 12:04:33	@KAPT_Kipper	Then we have the last of the networking in phase C. This one is going to be fun. They have to work around the live fibre connections
2015-06-04 12:05:29	+emptythevoid	what could go wrong
2015-06-04 12:06:46	+emptythevoid	I haven't had to deal with anytihng of that magnitude, but twice we moved one of our satellite sites from one location to a new one.  had to work with ATT, the network ops of the State of KY, and our local telco people to move the internet from one location to the other and have everything online in two days.  Do-able, and we got it done, but those vendors do not like to work together that quickly
2015-06-04 12:07:02	@KAPT_Kipper	Exactly- Since we are raising the floor 18" and the fibre has no slack and requires the rack to be moved up at the same time the shelves are moved down. 
2015-06-04 12:08:11	+emptythevoid	you're a braver person than I.  :)
2015-06-04 12:08:39	@KAPT_Kipper	This is a long project, since we have to move stuff, partial empty the room, wall off that section and renovate it. then move the gear from the old section to the new one. This was Phase A. B is the reno of that section except the network rack row. 
2015-06-04 12:09:50	@KAPT_Kipper	The last time the room was touched was 1989 and it showed. They are removing the asbestos ceiling tiles today.
2015-06-04 12:10:03	+emptythevoid	oh yuck
2015-06-04 12:10:10	+emptythevoid	the place I'm at now has that too
2015-06-04 12:10:16	+emptythevoid	and that's throughout the whole office
2015-06-04 12:10:29	@KAPT_Kipper	yep. Any public building from the 60's is full of that shite
2015-06-04 12:11:02	@KAPT_Kipper	I think it's a 1.2 million project.
2015-06-04 12:11:04	+emptythevoid	ours is the old electric co's central office.  There's so much exposed electrical mess in the ceiling, we couldn't even get an electrician to fix it all for us
2015-06-04 12:11:49	+emptythevoid	in fact, someone from the *new* electric office had to go up into our ceiling once and was all like "who did your electric wiring?!"
2015-06-04 12:11:53	@KAPT_Kipper	We ripped out all the electrical and re-did them to come from the ceiling instead of under the raised floors. Looks amazing now
2015-06-04 12:12:00	+emptythevoid	lucky
2015-06-04 12:13:01	@KAPT_Kipper	No luck. We are gutting the place as we go. Replacing all the panels, AC units and power feeds
